Reasoning: 
- cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper proposes a coordinated HARQ approach to improve network outage probability and users' fairness, which involves information transmission and coding techniques. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The proposed approach aims to improve the performance of wireless networks, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the coordination of multiple users in a wireless network, which can be viewed as a control problem. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper mentions the use of multiple antennas, which can be related to multimedia signal processing and transmission. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): Although not the main focus, the paper briefly mentions the security implications of the proposed approach, which can be relevant to this sub-category.
